ng fathers were crucial to the success of the early republic. But the economic decisions they made were just as pivotal, ensuring the general welfare and common defense of the United States for decades to come. Founding Choices explores these economic choices and their profound influence on American life, westward expansion, and influence abroad. Among the topics covered are finance, trade, and monetary and banking policy, with a focus on the factors guiding those policies and their end result. This book redresses the relative neglect of the economic achievements of the founders. It will be essential reading for historians and economists alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aBodenhorn, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngerman, Stanley L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrubb, Farley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrwin, Douglas A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrwin, Douglas A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKhan, B. Zorina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMargo, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMittal, Sonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRakove, Jack N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRousseau, Peter L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSylla, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSylla, Richard, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWallis, John Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeingast, Barry